The split fountain is very random on this print so each one is quite different and has a painted and distressed quality to it. Chuck whipped this little hottie up for the NY Dolls show at the Culture Room. It is on some sweet candy apple red paper at 18″x23″. The inks used are maroon, pink, white, and gray. Limited edition of 60 prints.

*All Orders postage paid in the U.S. and Canada.  For orders outside of North America, Please add $10 for shipping.  Please contact us at info@ironforgepress.com if there are any issues with the shipping of your order.

name: Kanye West Poster
description:
Kanye West is a robot from the past.  How do I know this?  His glasses are made of venetian blinds and that shit is 80’s as hell. Plus it is so tacky that only a robot with no sense of style would put them on.  AND, his name reminds me of the Will Smith box-office blunder Wild Wild West which had a giant robot spider thing in it.  Now I am thinking of Kool Moe Dee.  Damn it, Kanye… Damn it!  Oh yeah, we made a poster for his glow in the dark tour which is totally freakin’ rad.  Peep it, kid!  6 colors (Glow in the dark ink, fluorescent blue, pink, green, purple, clear varnish) on iridescent blue cardstock.  Get yours a.s.a.p. before the robots from the future travel into the past to steal the bills in your wallets and replace them with coupons for laser disks. Limited edition, only a couple prints left!

*All Orders postage paid in the U.S. and Canada.  For orders outside of North America, Please add $10 for shipping.  Please contact us at info@ironforgepress.com if there are any issues with the shipping of your order.

name: The Melvins Poster- Denver
description:
Ah, the days when you could see a woman who looked strikingly similar to your Aunt Tammy strip and rub her baby maker for $0.35.  A treasured time in the golden age of perversion.  The Melvins make us want to rub our baby makers for free, so Mutha-effin’ Chuck did the layout and colors and omar angulo did the illustration for this bad boy. Part of the “official tour series” for the Melvins. Look for them coming to your city soon! Limited edition of 100 prints.

*All Orders postage paid in the U.S. and Canada.  For orders outside of North America, Please add $10 for shipping.  Please contact us at info@ironforgepress.com if there are any issues with the shipping of your order.

name: Widespread Panic Poster
description: It was time to bust out the art Deco in poster form, and we did it with this fine Widespread Panic poster.  Purple, Blue, and Metallic Olive inks on white stock.  Send this to a friend as a postcard from Miami. Limited edition of 100 prints.

name: Cyndi Lauper and the True Colors 2008 Poster
description: We have worked for Cyndi in the past doing some merchandise design so it was a treat to do this poster recently for the True Colors show. My lesbian Ex-girlfriend went and said it was awesome and that Rosie O’Donnel played drums. When I hear Cyndi Lauper, I immediately think of The Goonies, and when I hear Rosie O’Donnel, I think of Dave Chappelle saying “she has dick holes in her underwear”. Two extremely fond memories for me so by all accounts, the True Colors Tour is in fact, awesome. The poster is 4 colors on red stock, 18×23. Limited edition of 50 prints.

name: Journey, Heart, and Cheap Trick Poster
description: New poster for Journey, Heart and Cheap Trick! 4 colors (orange, blue, metallic gold and black) on black cardstock. Basilio did the illustration, Chuck did the layout and colors like usual.  What did I do?  Well, I was on a dirtbike peeling-out in Steve Perry’s drive way trying to get him to come back for a reunion show.  He was having no part in that and decided to tickle my eyes and imagination by combing his feathered hair in a bath robe right in front of me.  Needless to say, the mission was a bitter-sweet success. Limited edition of 50 prints.

name: Chris Isaak w/Lisa Loeb Poster
description: Here we have a sweet print illustrated by John Kissee and of course, printed at the forge.  Teal, black, and a special color I do not have a name for.  We will call it Gary for the sake of this post.  Gary is a little opaque white and metallic silver pigment mixed with light green.  He is a real beauty.  With a color as exclusive as Gary on board, you better get one of these ordered right away before they disappear.  This baby is printed on our favorite natural chip-board at 17"x22". Limited edition of 150 prints.

name: Smashing Pumpkins Poster
description: Poster for the Smashing Pumpkins Boca Raton show. Design by the mighty Hydro74. White Pearlescent and Metallic Gold inks on black uncoated stock. Limited edition of 150 pcs.  16"x20" print on 18"x23" black stock.  Only a few remain, get yours quick!

name: The Melvins Poster - Phoenix
description: “That’s a good one” -Dale Crover  Yeah, he totally said that and we are totally stoked to have been invited to create this beauty.  Perfectly designed so you can decorate your out house at your fishing camp with some prime wall details.  This jam is 2 colors (black and metallic bronze) on chipboard. Awesome illustration by Mr. Scotty Baldwin. Limited edition of 120 prints.

name: Foo Fighters and Jimmy Eat World Poster
description: I don't know what a Foo is, but Dave Grohl is fighting the shit out of it.  Jimmy Eat World are in fact the chosen ones as proven by their initials.  Printed on 17.5″x22.5″ chipboard in purple, red, maroon, and gold. Designed by Chuck Loose for Live Nation. Limited edition of 150 prints.

name: Sonata Arctica Poster
description: 3 color screen print: white/metallic silver/tinted silver varnish on 140 lb. black card stock. A collabo between Chuck Loose/Iron Forge Press (illustration and printing) and Troy White Design (type treatment). Limited edition of 50 prints.

name: Misfits - Werewolf Poster
description:
16″ x 20″ 5 Color Print with metallic copper. Paper size, 18″ x 23″.
Here is an image of the new Misfits poster. Another collabo between Chuck Loose/Iron Forge Press (layout and printing) and Omar Angulo (illustration). Limited edition of 100 prints.

name: Exodus/Goatwhore Poster
description:
Of all the times I imagined hooking up with a demon-whore in a crock-pot, She never looked this good.
Here we have an awesome Exodus/GoatWhore Poster which was illustrated by Basilio here at Ironforge and put together by Chuck. Basilio, as you can see, totally kicks ass and we will be seeing a lot more of his amazing illustrations as we continue cranking out sweet poster prints. You can check out more Basilio business here: http://www.myspace.com/sevenbasilio Printed on 17.5″ x 22.5″ 20 pt. chipboard, this poser slays. Copper Metallic, Neon Pink, Metallic Gold, Maroon, Red and Black inks were thrown down to create this sweet treat. As usual, we have a limited # for sale. Limited edition of 90 prints.

name: Rush Poster
description:
Here is the latest masterpiece designed by Mr. Chuck Loose and printed by the masterful Basilio.  When not printing sweet clothing and kick-ass posters, we hang around conjuring the undead to do our bidding so this poster was a natural fit.  Jealous?

8.5″x21″ custom paper size on  140lb black stock.  Dark green, light green, orange, yellow, white pearlescent and black inks.  We also threw a couple of these on some plexiglass because the only thing cooler than a suncatcher is a Rush suncatcher.  Put this bad boy in your kitchen window, Grandma! Limited edition of 100 prints.

name: Queens of the Stone Age Poster - Playing Card
description: 4 color screen print: white/red/black/metallic silver on 17.5″x22″ 20 pt. chipboard. A collabo between Chuck Loose/Iron Forge Press (the queen of hearts side and printing) and Troy White Design (the ace of spades side). Limited edition of 150 prints.

name: Dethklok at Jannus Landing Poster
description:
This is the best poster we’ve done for a cartoon band (so far). P.S., Ian is in California and my funny bone hurts, so there will be more engaging commentary on these new posters when he returns. 7 colors, illustration by the mighty OMAR ANGULO

edit: By engaging commentary, he means I will come up with some random nonsense, link it to the poster we designed by a stroke of original and pure genius, and wrap it up with production details and a thank you sir. That ain’t happeing here. But this poster is freakin’ awesome. Limited edition of 50 prints.

name: Queens of the Stone Age Poster - Light Bulb
description: Here is the latest Queens of the Stone Age Poster Chuck designed. 16″x20″ print on 18″x23″ paper. Using Black and Glow ink. Limited edition of 150 prints.

name: Wu-Tang Clan Poster
description:
Update 6/30/08: this print is SOLD OUT!

Here we have a Wu-Tang Clan poster on 18″ x 23″ 14 pt. stock in a 8 color print. Ink colors we slapped down are Yellow, Blue, Red, Green, Black, Brown, Dark Brown, and Metallic Silver. Illustrated by Basilio here at ironforge. You can see more of his work and say hello here: http://www.myspace.com/sevenbasilio  We are an equal opportunity vendor, so any Robeast that would like a print to study Voltron before randomly materializing out of the sky and getting impaled by a giant robot sword is welcome to shop with us. Thanks! Limited edition of 150 prints.

name: The Mars Volta Poster
description: This is a real beauty we have here folks.  Basilio threw down this totally sick illustration and Chuck tricked it out with the perfect type treatment and color scheme.  What did I do?  I issued two sturdy pats on the back from the comfort of my office.  I am a sweetheart.  Here are the vital stats of this masterpiece:  18×23, 6 colors: metallic lemon, brown, green, red, microsphere green, black. This mutha done SOLD OUT!!!! Limited edition of 150 prints.

name: Bruce Springsteen Poster
description: Here is a hot item.  Our Bruce Springsteen poster sold out faster than a punk kid in college.  You can not buy one, but you may look on in glorious awe from here. Limited edition of 50 prints.
